## Working Style Rules

- **NEVER commit or push** — user handles all git operations
- **NEVER run destructive commands** (delete, drop, purge, uninstall) without showing the command first and waiting for approval
- **NEVER deploy to production** without explicit confirmation
- **ALWAYS show proposed changes** before applying them
- **Read-only operations are fine** without asking — get, describe, logs, cat, grep, ls
- **When stuck: ask, never guess** — say "I don't have this info, let me ask" rather than making assumptions
- **Complete logs only** — save full log files, analyze entirely, never work from snippets
- **For every new ticket** — create a folder immediately when work begins, not after it's resolved
- **For every new topic** — create a dedicated file in docs/ when it grows too large for this file
- **Update documentation as we work** — capture new knowledge immediately, don't leave it for later

[Add any project-specific rules here. Examples:]
- Never edit charts directly on the production server — always edit locally and deploy
- Always create a branch before making code changes, never work on main/master directly
- Run tests before marking any fix as complete

